<subSubSection id="C3261DE06662FFFB1984FCB5FC03EF22" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B834E6B6662FFFB1984FCB5FC03EF22" blockId="6.[192,1440,646,863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B94892796662FFFB1984FCB5FE85EF63" box="[240,348,774,798]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Remarks</emphasis>
. In their familial distribution map, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6662FFFB1A71FCB5FB93EF62" author="Gardner, M. R. &amp; R. M. Shelley" box="[773,1098,774,799]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="177 - 268" refId="ref14125" refString="Gardner, M. R., and R. M. Shelley. 1989. New records, species, and genera of caseyid millipeds from the Pacific Coast of North America (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida: Caseyidae). Pan-Pacific Entomologist 65 (2): 177 - 268." type="journal article" year="1989">Gardner and Shelley (1989</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 219) placed two symbols in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="49F880896662FFFB184AFC95FE3CEF43" box="[318,485,806,830]" country="United States of America" name="North Dakota" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">North Dakota</collectingRegion>
representing 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C35E86662FFFB1BFEFC94FCD2EF43" baseAuthorityName="Harger" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[650,779,806,830]" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Caseyidae" genus="Underwoodia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pezizales" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="iuloides">
<emphasis id="B94892796662FFFB1BFEFC94FCD2EF43" box="[650,779,806,830]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">U. iuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the genus and species were then unknown at these locations. Gonopodal illustrations are available in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD339A6662FFFB1A50FCF5FC0FEF22" author="Shelley, R. M." box="[804,982,838,863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="168 - 176" refId="ref15735" refString="Shelley, R. M. 1993. The milliped genus Underwoodia (Chordeumatida: Caseyidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology 71: 168 - 176." type="journal article" year="1993">Shelley (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
